rComments: Prof. Hummel is extremely helpful. If you don't understand something during lecture then be sure to go to his office hours. His exams are tricky, but he tries to test his best students. Take his class, you will learn chemistry :)

He's most definitely not a bad professor. He's a nice guy, he explains concepts well in lecture, and he'll answer any questions you have, but his exams are very hard. The kinds of questions he asks on exams are tricky and much more in depth than homework problems or quiz questions, so you really have to put an effort into the class to succeed.
Good professor who told you what he wanted you to learn and then expected you to learn it. Some of the exams were difficult, but they were always curved.

I really enjoyed Hummel's class. His lectures were interesting, and he mixed in demonstrations to keep people involved. The class was not too difficult, but it can be if you do not do the homework problems or do not study for the tests. I would recommend the past exam booklet. I was not looking forward to chem, but I ended up liking the class!

Great professor. Very understanding and his lectures are interesting. He is very laid back with attendance, and is very approachable. Very good guy to go and see if you have a problem or if you are not doing well. The best chem 102 teacher, if not more, just had him in 102. would go out of my way to get him again for sure.
He is a great professor.  He explains all of the concepts clearly and makes good use of the materials he gives out.  His tests are challenging but fair.
He is a really nice professor, and his favorite word is "goofy". I heard stories that he gives money to people who correct him :)
Hes a great teacher but the class is kind of hard! Study and do homework you'll be fine!
Hes a great teacher but the class is kind of hard! Study and do homework you'll be fine!
Good teacher, knows his stuff and communicates concepts well

Professor Hummel is not a great professor only to those who enjoy chemistry. He talks way too fast, does easy example problems in class, and expects you to master problems that he says are designed for the "smartest student." His exams are hard. I recommend that you actually have a good background chemistry before entering this class.
Funny, knows what hes talking about, keeps the students attention
Super fun to listen to when in lecture. Likes to do a lot of different presentations to show what we are learning (especially things that involve explosions).

He definitely lives up to his name as Tricky Tom Hummel, yet is an amazing professor. He truly does have the students best interest at heart. Do not hesitate to go ask him for any questions, he is so helpful. Get to know him, and really put forth a strong effort in his class it will pay off. I had to work very hard to get a B, so don't expect a goo

I came into the class only taking it because it was required for me.  I hated chemistry as it was, and altough "Tricky Tom" could be humorous, I found him really hard to follow because he talked so fast and I had never had any idea what was going on. However I had an awesome TA and that helped alot. But this class sucked for me, and I really tried.
I'm never bored in his lectures!

Great lecturer. Very animated and funny, keeps material interesting. May talk fast at times, but his explanations are great if you keep up. His exams are quite hard, but perfectly possible if you keep up with the material.
He is so funny. He is a good teacher, but you need to study on your own. You need to do practice problems if you want your A. He is extremely nice and approachable.
Hummel is a tough but really good professor and he makes class funny.

I'm laughing about every five minutes in class, and he does a lot of experiments (mostly blowing things up) that are very interesting.  I think he explains things extremely well.  If you're a slacker, you'll have a hard time with the tests.  But if you honestly try, I think an A or B won't be impossible to get.
